%RECOVERY :+
   Use%RECOVERY+to turn RECOVERY mode on or off.
   If RECOVERY mode is on when a system crash occurs, automatic recovery
   take place the next time that you attempt to use edit.
   RECOVERY mode is remembered in your edit profile. The default setting
   a new edit profile is RECOVERY off.
   If any changes have been made to the data, turning RECOVERY mode on c
   the data to be immediately written to a temporary%backup+file. If no
   have been made to the data, turning RECOVERY mode on simply changes t
   current edit profile. When the first change is made to the data, it i
   written to the backup file.

   More topic will be presented in the EDIT tutorial.
+
+Enter%&EPF+to exit the tutorial and return to the EDIT modes control pa
+Hit%ENTER+to go on to the next tutorial panel
)INIT
  &EPF = PFK(END)
  IF (&EPF = &Z)
    &EPF = 'END'
  &D = TRUNC(&EPF,2)
  &DT = .TRAIL
  &D = TRUNC(&DT,1)
  IF (&D = '0')
    &DT = .TRAIL
    &EPF = 'PF&DT'
)PROC
)END
